hed to accompany his wonderfully inscrutable exhibition Forlesen at the Renaissance Society at the University of Chicago, Pope.L: Showing Up to Withhold is simultaneously an artist’s book and a monograph. In addition to reproductions of a number of his most recent artworks, it includes images of significant works from the past decade, and presents a forum for reflection and analysis on art making today with contributions by renowned critics and scholars, including Lawrie Balfour, Nick Bastis, Lauren Berlant, and K. Silem Mohammad.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aArt, Americany21st centuryvExhibitions. 0aInstallations (Art)vExhibitions. 7aART / General.2bisacsh1 aBalfour, Lawrie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBastis, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerlant, Lauren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMohammad, K. Silem, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPope, L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReimer, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226200231423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226200231.jpg  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles